==English==

===Etymology===
From '''iso''', ''[[same]]'' + chronous, [[time]]

===Adjective===
'''isochronous'''
#happening at [[regular]] [[interval]]s
#happening at the same [[time]]; [[isochronal]]
#{{computing}} of or pertaining to the use of the same clock throughout a network
#: ''Their entire national telephone network is isochronous, with a clock distribution tree radiating from a cesium clock.'' <!-- if it has a clock distribution tree, then it has more than one clock!! -->
#{{computing}} of or pertaining to data associated with time sensitive application
#: ''These packets belong to an isochronous voice application and need priority handling.''
